					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">And if you square the coefficients, you get either a triangle wave or a circle wave.<br /><br />∑ cos(x)/x²<br /><br /><ul><li>cos(x) + cos(3x)/9 + cos(5x)/25 + cos(7x)/49 + cos(9x)/81: <a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=cos%28x%29+%2B+cos%283x%29%2F9+%2B+cos%285x%29%2F25+%2B+cos%287x%29%2F49" class="postlink">Triangle wave</a></li><li>cos(x) - cos(3x)/9 + cos(5x)/25 - cos(7x)/49 + cos(9x)/81: <a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=cos%28x%29+-+cos%283x%29%2F9+%2B+cos%285x%29%2F25+-+cos%287x%29%2F49+%2B+cos%289x%29%2F81" class="postlink">Circle wave</a></li><li>sin(x) + sin(3x)/9 + sin(5x)/25 + sin(7x)/49 + sin(9x)/81: <a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=sin%28x%29+%2B+sin%283x%29%2F9+%2B+sin%285x%29%2F25+%2B+sin%287x%29%2F49+%2B+sin%289x%29%2F81" class="postlink">Circle wave</a></li><li>sin(x) - sin(3x)/9 + sin(5x)/25 - sin(7x)/49 + sin(9x)/81: <a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=sin%28x%29+-+sin%283x%29%2F9+%2B+sin%285x%29%2F25+-+sin%287x%29%2F49+%2B+sin%289x%29%2F81" class="postlink">Triangle wave</a></li></ul><br />But for an &quot;NES triangle&quot; sound, the 31st and 33rd harmonics of the stairstep output are important, as <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=13243" class="postlink">I've demonstrated elsewhere</a>. Let's add those:<br /><br /><ul><li>cos(x) + cos(3x)/9 + cos(5x)/25 + cos(7x)/49 + cos(9x)/81 + cos(31x)/31 - cos(33x)/33 - cos(63x)/63 + cos(65x)/65: <a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=cos%28x%29+%2B+cos%283x%29%2F9+%2B+cos%285x%29%2F25+%2B+cos%287x%29%2F49+%2B+cos%289x%29%2F81+%2B+cos%2831x%29%2F31+-+cos%2833x%29%2F33+-+cos%2863x%29%2F63+%2B+cos%2865x%29%2F65" class="postlink">Triangle wave with stair steps</a></li></ul></div>

