						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">nitro2k01 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">As it turns out, the sinc function <em>is</em> somewhat related to the square wave harmonic coefficients.</div><br />I was taught that a square wave contains every harmonic in it. This is one of the reasons why oscilloscopes include a square wave generator: if you feed it back to the oscillator, and notice some distortion in the corners (i.e. they aren't as sharp as they should be) it means some frequency range is getting filtered out, which means there's a problem you should fix to avoid getting invalid results when doing actual work.</div>

